## 15. Product Features (Detailed)

### 15.1 AI Module
- CNN-based classifier (EfficientNet-B0, transfer-learned on ImageNet weights, fine-tuned on NEU-DET)
- Output: defect class + confidence score
- Grad-CAM computed on the final convolutional block, overlaid on the original image
- Model served via a FastAPI inference endpoint (single model instance, loaded at startup)

### 15.2 Image Inspection
- Drag-and-drop or file-picker upload
- Client-side validation (file type, size limit e.g. 5MB)
- Server returns class, confidence, Grad-CAM image (base64 or stored URL)
- Result and Grad-CAM displayed side-by-side with original image
- Every result persisted to `inspections` table

### 15.3 Live Inspection
- Browser requests webcam access (`getUserMedia`)
- Frame captured and sent to backend at a fixed interval (e.g. every 1–2 seconds — **not** every video frame, to stay within CPU inference budget)
- Prediction displayed as an overlay/label in near-real-time
- If confidence for a defect class exceeds a threshold (e.g. 70%), frame is automatically saved and logged as an inspection record

### 15.4 Dashboard
- Total inspections counter
- Total defects detected counter
- Defect-class distribution (bar or pie chart)
- Recent inspections table (last N entries)
- Basic date-range filter

### 15.5 Authentication
- Registration (email, password, name)
- Login issuing JWT access token
- Logout (client-side token discard; optional short-lived token strategy)
- Protected routes via JWT middleware in FastAPI

