## 22. Risks and Mitigation

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|---|---|---|---|
| Live webcam inference too slow on CPU | High | High | Cap frame-send rate (1 frame/1-2s); downscale frames before inference; fall back to "near-live" polling instead of true real-time if needed |
| Grad-CAM implementation issues with EfficientNet's architecture | Medium | Medium | Use a well-tested library (`pytorch-grad-cam`) instead of hand-rolling; target the last MBConv block explicitly |
| Model accuracy below target due to small dataset | Medium | High | Use transfer learning + aggressive data augmentation; document a lower achieved accuracy honestly rather than overclaiming |
| Scope creep (adding "nice to have" features) | High | High | Enforce MVP list strictly; anything new goes into Section 26 (Future Enhancements) |
| Running out of time near submission | Medium | High | Follow the Day 45 milestone plan with checkpoints (Section 28); if a checkpoint slips by >2 days, cut scope immediately, don't "catch up later" |
| Auth/security shortcuts causing vulnerabilities | Medium | Medium | Use established libraries (passlib/bcrypt, python-jose) rather than custom crypto |
| Dataset class imbalance | Medium | Medium | Check class distribution early; apply weighted loss or augmentation if imbalanced |

