## 25. MVP Definition

The MVP is considered complete when a logged-in user can:
1. Register and log in.
2. Upload an image and receive a defect classification with confidence score and Grad-CAM overlay.
3. Use the webcam for live detection with visible, reasonably responsive predictions.
4. See their inspection automatically saved and reflected in a dashboard with basic stats and charts.
5. Log out, and be unable to access inspection/dashboard routes without logging back in.

Anything beyond this is a stretch goal, not an MVP blocker.

