## 28. 45-Day Development Milestones (with Checkpoints)

Each week ends in a **checkpoint** — a hard go/no-go review. If a checkpoint is missed, cut scope for the next phase immediately rather than trying to "catch up" — that's how projects blow their deadline.

| Phase | Days | Deliverable | ✅ Checkpoint (End of Phase) |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Phase 1: Setup & Data** | 1–5 | Repo structure, environment setup, NEU-DET dataset acquired and explored, train/val/test split defined | **CP1:** Dataset loaded, class distribution documented, environment reproducible via `requirements.txt`/Docker |
| **Phase 2: Model Training** | 6–15 | EfficientNet-B0 fine-tuned, augmentation pipeline, training/validation loop, initial accuracy benchmark | **CP2:** Model achieves ≥85% val accuracy; best checkpoint saved; training curves documented |
| **Phase 3: Grad-CAM & Model Finalization** | 16–20 | Grad-CAM integrated and validated on sample predictions; final model exported (.pt/.onnx) | **CP3:** Grad-CAM visually correct on ≥10 test images; final model accuracy ≥90% documented |
| **Phase 4: Backend – Auth & Core API** | 21–26 | FastAPI project, user model, JWT auth, PostgreSQL schema/migrations, image upload endpoint wired to model | **CP4:** Can register/login via API (Postman/curl) and get a real prediction back from an uploaded image, end-to-end |
| **Phase 5: Backend – Live & Dashboard APIs** | 27–31 | Live-frame inference endpoint, inspection history endpoints, dashboard aggregation endpoints | **CP5:** All backend endpoints tested and documented (e.g. via FastAPI's auto-generated docs); response times measured |
| **Phase 6: Frontend – Auth & Image Inspection UI** | 32–36 | React app scaffold, Tailwind setup, login/register pages, image upload + result UI wired to backend | **CP6:** A user can log in through the UI and get a real prediction with Grad-CAM displayed |
| **Phase 7: Frontend – Live Inspection & Dashboard UI** | 37–40 | Webcam capture UI, live prediction display, dashboard charts and history table | **CP7:** Full user journey (Section 16) works start to finish in the browser |
| **Phase 8: Integration Testing & Bug Fixing** | 41–43 | End-to-end testing, edge case handling (bad files, expired tokens, empty states), performance tuning | **CP8:** No known crash-causing bugs; all Acceptance Criteria (Section 27) pass manually |
| **Phase 9: Documentation & Demo Prep** | 44–45 | Final report, README, model card, demo script/rehearsal | **CP9 (Final):** Project runs cleanly from a fresh clone/Docker Compose; demo rehearsed at least once end-to-end |

**Non-negotiable checkpoint rule:** if you're not at ≥85% val accuracy by Day 15 (CP2), do not proceed to polishing Grad-CAM — stop and fix the model first. A broken model with a beautiful UI is a failed project; a strong model with a plain UI is a passing one.

